  heroTag:"📸 Photography Guide · 7 min read",
  faq:[
    {q:"What is the best photography spot in Dubai?",a:"The Dubai Fountain at sunset from Dubai Mall waterfront — Burj Khalifa glowing gold, fountain performing, entire Downtown skyline visible. For unique angles: Al Fahidi wind towers with modern towers visible behind. For aerial: Burj Khalifa Level 124 at the last slot of the day."},
    {q:"What time is golden hour in Dubai?",a:"Golden hour is approximately 45 minutes after sunrise and 45 minutes before sunset. In winter: sunrise 6:00–6:30 AM, sunset 5:45–6:15 PM. In summer: sunrise 5:30 AM, sunset 7:00 PM. Blue hour (best for skylines) begins immediately after sunset and lasts 20–40 minutes."},
    {q:"Can you use a drone in Dubai for photography?",a:"Drone photography in Dubai requires a UAE Civil Aviation Authority licence and advance registration. Most tourist areas (Marina, Downtown, Palm) are restricted airspace — no drones permitted without specific clearance. The Dubai Desert Conservation Reserve also restricts drones. Unauthorised drone flying carries heavy fines. Phone cameras and standard cameras are unrestricted."},
  ],
  sections:[
    {type:"intro", animId:"camera-lens", animLabel:"📷 Dubai Photography — 20 Locations & Timing",
     content:`<strong>Dubai is arguably the most photogenic built environment on Earth.</strong> The density of architectural icons within a compact city means every direction has a shot. The challenge is not finding good spots — it is knowing when to shoot each one. <em>The difference between a tourist snapshot and a portfolio image in Dubai is almost entirely timing.</em>`},
    {type:"heading", text:"Top 10 Spots with", textEm:"Exact Timing"},
    {type:"timeline", items:[
      {time:"1. Dubai Fountain at sunset", text:"Best: 30min before sunset + fountain show · f/8, ISO 200, 1/500s · Avoid midday completely"},
      {time:"2. Dubai Marina blue hour", text:"Best: 40min after sunset · Wide angle 16mm from the bridge · Long exposure for reflections · f/2.8, ISO 1600, 8s on tripod"},
      {time:"3. Desert sunrise (balloon/camel)", text:"<strong>Best single shot in Dubai.</strong> 5:48 AM golden light · f/8, ISO 400, 1/800s · The most cinematic moment available"},
      {time:"4. Al Fahidi wind towers", text:"Best: 9 AM morning light from east · Modern towers visible behind heritage buildings · Layers in one frame"},
      {time:"5. Kite Beach + Burj Al Arab", text:"Best: Morning golden hour · Camera pointing south along the beach · Burj Al Arab on horizon"},
      {time:"6. Dubai Frame sky bridge", text:"Best: 1hr before sunset · Old Dubai in warm light looking north, modern city looking south"},
      {time:"7. Creek Harbour promenade", text:"Best: 1hr before sunset · Burj Khalifa on western horizon, flamingos sometimes visible"},
      {time:"8. Atlantis from Palm crescent", text:"Best: Golden hour · AED 25 monorail ride gives you the angle"},
      {time:"9. Old Dubai abra crossing", text:"Best: Dusk · Ochre buildings in warm light, abra silhouette · f/4, ISO 800"},
      {time:"10. Burj Khalifa Level 124", text:"Best: Pre-book last slot of day (sunset + blue hour from above) · Most comprehensive city view"},
    ]},
    {type:"ratings", items:[{icon:"📸",val:"20",label:"Unique spots"},{icon:"🌅",label:"Golden hour: always"},{icon:"🎈",label:"Balloon: best aerial"},{icon:"🌙",label:"Blue hour: skylines"}]},
  ]
